        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; 10 appears from internal evidence to be by a different author (see the introduction of the Book of Nehemiah).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The last two clauses of Nehemiah 7:73 should stand as the beginning of Nehemiah 8 (as in the Septuagint). The text would then run: \"And when the seventh month was come, and the children of Israel were in their cities, the whole people gathered themselves together as one man,\" etc. Compare the margin reference. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "The last two clauses of ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Nehemiah 7:73",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " should stand as the beginning of ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Nehemiah 8",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " (as in the Septuagint). The text would then run: \"And when the seventh month was come, and the children of Israel were in their cities, the whole people gathered themselves together as one man,\" etc. Compare the margin reference. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
